<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000018#     2#        287.2#">Va. Code Ann. § 18.2-287.2</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_18.2-287.2"/><heading><desig>§ 18.2-287.2.</desig><title>Wearing of body armor while committing a crime; penalty</title></heading><bodyText><p>Any person who, while committing a crime of violence as defined in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 18.2-288"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 18.2-288">§ 18.2-288 (2)<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000018#     2#          288#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or a felony violation of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 18.2-248"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 18.2-248">§ 18.2-248<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000018#     2#          248#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or subdivision (a) 2 or 3 of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 18.2-248.1"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 18.2-248.1">§ 18.2-248.1<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000018#     2#        248.1#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, has in his possession a firearm or knife and is wearing body armor designed to diminish the effect of the impact of a bullet or projectile shall be guilty of a Class 4 felony.</p></bodyText><history><hi